Here..."><p>Unveiling the Western Digital Blue SN570 250GB NVMe SSD</p><p>Do you want to achieve professional level tracking and responsiveness that allows you to outplay your opponents in every single frame? We are excited to present the Western Digital Blue SN570 250GB M.2 2280 PCIe NVMe SSD which is a true game changer for creative professionals and gamers alike. This high performance internal drive is designed for those who demand the absolute fastest boot times and reliable storage for their essential applications. We have selected this model because it delivers up to 5X the performance of our best SATA SSDs. Whether you are editing photos in Photoshop or loading into a competitive match we ensure this SSD provides the precision you need. You can get this elite storage solution from PCB Store for the best price in Bangladesh.</p><p><br></p><p>Unmatched Performance and Technical Specifications</p><p>We know that speed and reliability are the most important factors for any serious PC build. The Western Digital Blue SN570 250GB is powered by advanced 3D TLC NAND flash technology. This architecture is widely regarded as one of the best for balancing performance and endurance. We have verified that this drive provides flawless sequential read speeds of up to 3300MB/s and write speeds of 1200MB/s. No more waiting. No more lag. Just pure performance.</p><p><br></p><p>The standout feature of this SSD is the PCIe Gen3 x4 NVMe v1.4 interface. While standard SATA drives are limited to around 550MB/s we have enabled this drive to shatter those barriers. This reduces system boot times to mere seconds and ensures that heavy applications like Premiere Pro or InDesign launch almost instantly. This level of responsiveness is perfect for users who value their time and productivity. It is built to keep up with your imagination.</p><p><br></p><p>We also equipped this drive with built-in reliability features to protect your brilliant work. The SN570 features a Total Bytes Written (TBW) rating of 150. This ensures that your storage remains healthy and stable for years to come even under consistent daily use. We also included access to the Western Digital SSD Dashboard. This downloadable software helps you monitor your drive's health available space and temperature in real time. It is built for the grind.</p><p><br></p><p>Why You Will Love the WD Blue SN570</p><p>We believe the biggest benefit of the Western Digital Blue SN570 is the total creative freedom it gives you. The slim M.2 2280 form factor allows us to save massive amounts of space inside your system. You can pack a lot of performance into your small form factor PC or thin laptop with just a single NVMe slot. It makes your build look cleaner and promotes better airflow.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>The added value for creators is another feature you will love. We want to inspire your next passion project so this SSD often includes a one month membership to Adobe Creative Cloud. This gives you access to the world's best creative apps like Photoshop and Lightroom. It is a unique touch that helps you get started on your creative journey immediately after installation. It looks great on any spec sheet.</p><p><br></p><p>The energy efficient design is engineered to maintain low power consumption while delivering high speed. We optimized the firmware to ensure that your laptop battery lasts longer compared to using older storage technologies. This allows for longer editing sessions or gaming marathons without needing to reach for a charger. You work faster. You create more. You succeed.</p><p><br></p><p>Design and Built for Excellence</p><p>The Western Digital Blue SN570 features a single sided PCB design that ensures compatibility with almost any modern motherboard or laptop. We designed the layout to be thermally efficient allowing it to run cool without the need for bulky heatsinks. It fits perfectly into slim designs. It feels natural in any high end build.</p><p><br></p><p>For connectivity we ensured that this drive is backward compatible with older PCIe generations. This ensures that your investment remains stable even if you are upgrading an older system. The physical dimensions are a standard 80mm by 22mm making it easy to handle during the installation process. We make sure you are never stuck with incompatible hardware.</p><p><br></p><p>We also made sure that data migration is easy to manage. You can download Acronis True Image for Western Digital to clone your existing drive to the new SN570. This allows you to transfer your entire operating system and files without reinstalling everything from scratch. This level of convenience ensures that the transition to NVMe speed is as smooth as possible. It is your data. Your way.</p><p><br></p><p>Your Purchase Journey at PCB Store</p><p>You can buy the Western Digital Blue SN570 250GB M.2 2280 PCIe NVMe SSD from PCB Store today. &lt;p&gt;Do you want to achieve professional level tracking and responsiveness that allows you to outplay your opponents in every single frame? We are excited to present the Western Digital Blue SN570 250GB M.2 2280 PCIe NVMe SSD which is a true game changer for creative professionals and gamers alike. This high performance internal drive is designed for those who demand the absolute fastest boot times and reliable storage for their essential applications. We have selected this model because it delivers up to 5X the performance of our best SATA SSDs. Whether you are editing photos in Photoshop or loading into a competitive match we ensure this SSD provides the precision you need. You can get this elite storage solution from PCB Store for the best price in Bangladesh.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unmatched Performance and Technical Specifications&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We know that speed and reliability are the most important factors for any serious PC build. The Western Digital Blue SN570 250GB is powered by advanced 3D TLC NAND flash technology. This architecture is widely regarded as one of the best for balancing performance and endurance. We have verified that this drive provides flawless sequential read speeds of up to 3300MB/s and write speeds of 1200MB/s. No more waiting. No more lag. Just pure performance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The standout feature of this SSD is the PCIe Gen3 x4 NVMe v1.4 interface. While standard SATA drives are limited to around 550MB/s we have enabled this drive to shatter those barriers. This reduces system boot times to mere seconds and ensures that heavy applications like Premiere Pro or InDesign launch almost instantly. This level of responsiveness is perfect for users who value their time and productivity. It is built to keep up with your imagination.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We also equipped this drive with built-in reliability features to protect your brilliant work. The SN570 features a Total Bytes Written (TBW) rating of 150. This ensures that your storage remains healthy and stable for years to come even under consistent daily use. We also included access to the Western Digital SSD Dashboard. This downloadable software helps you monitor your drive's health available space and temperature in real time. It is built for the grind.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Why You Will Love the WD Blue SN570&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We believe the biggest benefit of the Western Digital Blue SN570 is the total creative freedom it gives you. The slim M.2 2280 form factor allows us to save massive amounts of space inside your system. You can pack a lot of performance into your small form factor PC or thin laptop with just a single NVMe slot. It makes your build look cleaner and promotes better airflow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The added value for creators is another feature you will love. We want to inspire your next passion project so this SSD often includes a one month membership to Adobe Creative Cloud. This gives you access to the world's best creative apps like Photoshop and Lightroom. It is a unique touch that helps you get started on your creative journey immediately after installation. It looks great on any spec sheet.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The energy efficient design is engineered to maintain low power consumption while delivering high speed. We optimized the firmware to ensure that your laptop battery lasts longer compared to using older storage technologies. This allows for longer editing sessions or gaming marathons without needing to reach for a charger. You work faster. You create more. You succeed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Design and Built for Excellence&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Western Digital Blue SN570 features a single sided PCB design that ensures compatibility with almost any modern motherboard or laptop. We designed the layout to be thermally efficient allowing it to run cool without the need for bulky heatsinks. It fits perfectly into slim designs. It feels natural in any high end build.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For connectivity we ensured that this drive is backward compatible with older PCIe generations. This ensures that your investment remains stable even if you are upgrading an older system. The physical dimensions are a standard 80mm by 22mm making it easy to handle during the installation process. We make sure you are never stuck with incompatible hardware.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We also made sure that data migration is easy to manage. You can download Acronis True Image for Western Digital to clone your existing drive to the new SN570. This allows you to transfer your entire operating system and files without reinstalling everything from scratch. This level of convenience ensures that the transition to NVMe speed is as smooth as possible. It is your data. Your way.&lt;/p&gt;

    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
            var themeColor = "#ee456b";
            var themeHoverColor = "#fee5e8";
            document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--theme-color', themeColor);
            document.documentElement.style.setProperty('--theme-hover-bg', themeHoverColor);

            // manage menu active svg color
            var svgImages = document.querySelectorAll(".menu.active .menu-icon");
            changeSvgImageColor(svgImages, themeColor);

            var selectedSvgImage;
            var svgColor;
            if (document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-primary img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-primary img");
                svgColor = themeColor;
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }

            if (document.querySelectorAll(".btn-primary img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".btn-primary img");
                svgColor = "#ffffff";
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }

            if (document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-info img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-info img");
                svgColor = "#0ea5e9";
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }

            if (document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-warning img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-warning img");
                svgColor = "#f97316";
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }

            if (document.querySelectorAll(".btn-danger img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".btn-danger img");
                svgColor = "#ffffff";
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }

            if (document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-danger img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-danger img");
                svgColor = "#ef4444";
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }

            if (document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-success img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".btn-outline-success img");
                svgColor = "#059669";
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }

            if (document.querySelectorAll(".svg-bg img")) {
                selectedSvgImage = document.querySelectorAll(".svg-bg img");
                svgColor = themeColor;
                changeSvgImageColor(selectedSvgImage, svgColor);
            }
        });

        function changeSvgImageColor(svgImages, svgColor, defaultColor = "#25314C") {
            svgImages.forEach(function(svgImage) {
                var svgPath = svgImage.getAttribute("src");
                var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
                xhr.onreadystatechange = function() {
                    if (xhr.readyState === 4 && xhr.status === 200) {
                        var svgContent = xhr.responseText;

                        const strokeRegex = new RegExp(`stroke="${defaultColor}"`, 'g');
                        const fillRegex = new RegExp(`fill="${defaultColor}"`, 'g');

                        svgContent = svgContent.replace(strokeRegex, `stroke="${svgColor}"`);
                        svgContent = svgContent.replace(fillRegex, `fill="${svgColor}"`);

                        svgImage.src = "data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8," + encodeURIComponent(svgContent);
                    }
                };
                xhr.open("GET", svgPath, true);
                xhr.send();
            });
        }

        // Fetch Admin Notifications
        const fetchAdminNotifications = () => {
            $.ajax({
                type: 'GET',
                url: "https://admin.pcbstore.net/admin/latest-orders",
                data: {
                    _token: "fGf5ktHdz9MIMAQBqGMyuQCba8Luc7jjb6vhvVtE"
                },
                dataType: 'json',
                success: function(response) {
                    $('#totalNotify').text(response.total_unread)
                    $('#notifications').empty()
                    $.each(response.orders, function(key, value) {
                        var id = value.id;
                        var link = "https://admin.pcbstore.net/admin/orders/:id/show";
                        link = link.replace(':id', id);
                        $('#notifications').append(
                            `<a href="${link}" class="item d-flex gap-2 align-items-center">
                            <div class="notification w-100 unread }">
                                <div class="userName">
                                    <p class="massTitle">${value.order_code} </p>
                                    <span class="time">${value.created_at}</span>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="description"></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </a>`
                        );
                    })
                },
                error: function(e) {
                    $('#notifications').empty()
                    if (e.status == 401 || e.status == 403) {
                        $('#totalNotify').text(0)
                        $("#notifications").html("emply");
                    } else {
                        $("#notifications").html(e.responseText);
                    }
                }
            });
        }

        // fetch shop notifications
        const fetchShopNotifications = () => {
            $.ajax({
                type: 'GET',
                url: "https://admin.pcbstore.net/admin/new-notifications",
                data: {
                    _token: "fGf5ktHdz9MIMAQBqGMyuQCba8Luc7jjb6vhvVtE"
                },
                dataType: 'json',
                success: function(response) {
                    $('#totalNotify').text(response.data.total)
                    $('#notifications').empty()
                    $.each(response.data.notifications, function(key, value) {
                        var id = value.id;
                        var link = "https://admin.pcbstore.net/admin/notification/:id/read";
                        link = link.replace(':id', id);
                        $('#notifications').append(
                            `<a href="${link}" class="item d-flex gap-2 align-items-center">
                            <div class="iconBox ${value.type == 'danger' ? 'cardIcon' : 'pdfIcon'}">
                                <i class="bi ${value.icon}"></i>
                            </div>
                            <div class="notification w-100 ${!value.is_read ? 'unread' : ''}">
                                <div class="userName">
                                    <p class="massTitle">${value.title} </p>
                                    <span class="time">${value.time}</span>
                                </div>
                                <div>
                                    <p class="description">${value.content}</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </a>`
                        );
                    })
                },
                error: function(e) {
                    $('#notifications').empty()
                    if (e.status == 401 || e.status == 403) {
                        $('#totalNotify').text(0)
                        $("#notifications").html("empty");
                    } else {
                        $("#notifications").html(e.responseText);
                    }
                }
            });
        }
    </script>

    <script>
        const Toast = Swal.mixin({
            toast: true,
            position: 'top-end',
            showConfirmButton: false,
            timer: 3000,
            timerProgressBar: true,
            didOpen: (toast) => {

        <script src="https://unpkg.com/quill-table-ui@1.0.5/dist/umd/index.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
    <script>
        const categorySearch = document.getElementById('categorySearch');
        const categoryTree = document.getElementById('categoryTree');
        let categorySearchTimeout;
        const filterCategoryTree = () => {
            const q = (categorySearch?.value || '').trim().toLowerCase();
            const root = categoryTree?.querySelector('.category-tree');
            if (!root) return;

            const traverse = (li, forceShow = false) => {
                const childUl = li.querySelector(':scope > ul');
                const labelText = (li.querySelector(':scope > label, :scope > span, :scope > a')?.textContent || li
                    .textContent).toLowerCase();
                const isMatch = q.length > 0 && labelText.includes(q);

                if (forceShow) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.toggle('match', isMatch);
                    if (childUl) {
                        childUl.style.display = '';
                        Array.from(childUl.children).forEach(child => {
                            if (child.tagName === 'LI') traverse(child, true);
                        });
                    }
                    return true;
                }

                let childHasMatch = false;
                if (childUl) {
                    const liChildren = Array.from(childUl.children).filter(c => c.tagName === 'LI');
                    liChildren.forEach(child => {
                        const res = traverse(child, false);
                        childHasMatch = childHasMatch || res;
                    });
                }

                if (q.length === 0) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    if (childUl) childUl.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.remove('match');
                    return true;
                }

                if (isMatch) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.add('match');
                    if (childUl) {
                        childUl.style.display = '';
                        Array.from(childUl.children).forEach(child => {
                            if (child.tagName === 'LI') traverse(child, true);
                        });
                    }
                    return true;
                }

                if (childHasMatch) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.remove('match');
                    if (childUl) childUl.style.display = '';
                    return true;
                }

                li.style.display = 'none';
                li.classList.remove('match');
                if (childUl) childUl.style.display = 'none';
                return false;
            };

            Array.from(root.children).forEach(el => {
                if (el.tagName === 'LI') traverse(el, false);
            });
        };



        // Category Attribute Search Implementation
        const categoryAttributeSearch = document.getElementById('categoryAttributeSearch');
        const categoryAttributeTree = document.querySelector('.categoryAttribute');
        let categoryAttributeSearchTimeout;

        const filterCategoryAttributeTree = () => {
            const q = (categoryAttributeSearch?.value || '').trim().toLowerCase();
            const root = categoryAttributeTree?.querySelector('.categoryAttribute-tree');
            if (!root) return;

            const traverse = (li, forceShow = false) => {
                const childUl = li.querySelector(':scope > ul');
                const labelText = (li.querySelector(':scope > label, :scope > span, :scope > a')?.textContent || li
                    .textContent).toLowerCase();
                const isMatch = q.length > 0 && labelText.includes(q);

                if (forceShow) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.toggle('match', isMatch);
                    if (childUl) {
                        childUl.style.display = '';
                        Array.from(childUl.children).forEach(child => {
                            if (child.tagName === 'LI') traverse(child, true);
                        });
                    }
                    return true;
                }

                let childHasMatch = false;
                if (childUl) {
                    const liChildren = Array.from(childUl.children).filter(c => c.tagName === 'LI');
                    liChildren.forEach(child => {
                        const res = traverse(child, false);
                        childHasMatch = childHasMatch || res;
                    });
                }

                if (q.length === 0) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    if (childUl) childUl.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.remove('match');
                    return true;
                }

                if (isMatch) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.add('match');
                    if (childUl) {
                        childUl.style.display = '';
                        Array.from(childUl.children).forEach(child => {
                            if (child.tagName === 'LI') traverse(child, true);
                        });
                    }
                    return true;
                }

                if (childHasMatch) {
                    li.style.display = '';
                    li.classList.remove('match');
                    if (childUl) childUl.style.display = '';
                    return true;
                }

                li.style.display = 'none';
                li.classList.remove('match');
                if (childUl) childUl.style.display = 'none';
                return false;
            };

            Array.from(root.children).forEach(el => {
                if (el.tagName === 'LI') traverse(el, false);
            });
        };

        const resetCategoryAttributeTree = () => {
            const root = categoryAttributeTree?.querySelector('.categoryAttribute-tree');
            if (!root) return;
            root.querySelectorAll('li').forEach(li => {
                li.style.display = '';
                const childUl = li.querySelector(':scope > ul');
                if (childUl) childUl.style.display = '';
                li.classList.remove('match');
            });
        };

        if (categoryAttributeSearch) {
            categoryAttributeSearch.addEventListener('input', () => {
                clearTimeout(categoryAttributeSearchTimeout);
                categoryAttributeSearchTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
                    if ((categoryAttributeSearch.value || '').trim().length === 0) {
                        resetCategoryAttributeTree();
                    } else {
                        filterCategoryAttributeTree();
                    }
                }, 200);
            });
        }

        const resetCategoryTree = () => {
            const root = categoryTree?.querySelector('.category-tree');
            if (!root) return;
            root.querySelectorAll('li').forEach(li => {
                li.style.display = '';
                const childUl = li.querySelector(':scope > ul');
                if (childUl) childUl.style.display = '';
                li.classList.remove('match');
            });
        };
        if (categorySearch) {
            categorySearch.addEventListener('input', () => {
                clearTimeout(categorySearchTimeout);
                categorySearchTimeout = setTimeout(() => {
                    if ((categorySearch.value || '').trim().length === 0) {
                        resetCategoryTree();
                    } else {
                        filterCategoryTree();
                    }
                }, 200);
            });
        }


        function toggleFields() {
            // Hide all fields
            document.getElementById('fileUploadField').classList.add('d-none');
            document.getElementById('youtubeField').classList.add('d-none');
            document.getElementById('vimeoField').classList.add('d-none');
            document.getElementById('dailymotionField').classList.add('d-none');

            // Get selected type
            const selectedType = document.getElementById('uploadType').value;

            // Show relevant field
            if (selectedType === 'file') {
                document.getElementById('fileUploadField').classList.remove('d-none');
            } else if (selectedType === 'youtube') {
                document.getElementById('youtubeField').classList.remove('d-none');
            } else if (selectedType === 'vimeo') {
                document.getElementById('vimeoField').classList.remove('d-none');
            } else if (selectedType === 'dailymotion') {
                document.getElementById('dailymotionField').classList.remove('d-none');
            }
        }

        function setupSku() {
            $(".selectSku").select2({
                tags: true,
                placeholder: "Write SKU and press (comma, space, or enter) to add separate SKUs",
                tokenSeparators: [',', ' ', 13]
            });
        }

        $(document).ready(function() {
            $(".selectTags").select2({
                tags: true,
                placeholder: "Write keywords and Press enter to add new one",
                tokenSeparators: [',', ' ', 13]
            });

            setupSku();
            $('.variationSelect2').select2();
        });


        function updateRowTotal($row, mainPrice) {
            const extraPrice = parseFloat($row.find('.extraPriceForm').val()) || 0;
            let extraDiscount = parseFloat($row.find('.extraDiscountPriceForm').val()) || 0;
            const totalExtraPrice = mainPrice + extraPrice;

            if (extraDiscount > totalExtraPrice) {
                extraDiscount = totalExtraPrice;
                $row.find('.extraDiscountPriceForm').val(0);
            }
            const totalPrice = totalExtraPrice - extraDiscount;
            $row.find('.totalVariationPrice').text(totalPrice.toFixed(2));
            $row.find('.totalVarPrice').text(totalExtraPrice.toFixed(2));
        }

        function updateAllRowsTotal() {
            const productPrice = parseFloat($('#price').val()) || 0;
            const productDiscountPrice = parseFloat($('#discount_price').val()) || 0;
            const mainPrice = productDiscountPrice > 0 ? productDiscountPrice : productPrice;

            $('.mainProductPrice').text(mainPrice);

            $('.row').each(function() {
                updateRowTotal($(this), mainPrice);
            });
        }

        $('#price, #discount_price').on('input', function() {
            updateAllRowsTotal();
        });

        $(document).on('input', '.extraPriceForm', function() {
            const $row = $(this).closest('.row');
            const productPrice = parseFloat($('#price').val()) || 0;
            const productDiscountPrice = parseFloat($('#discount_price').val()) || 0;
            const mainPrice = productDiscountPrice > 0 ? productDiscountPrice : productPrice;
            updateRowTotal($row, mainPrice);
        });
        $(document).on('input', '.extraDiscountPriceForm', function() {
            const $row = $(this).closest('.row');
            const value = parseFloat($(this).val()) || 0;
            const productPrice = parseFloat($('#price').val()) || 0;
            const productDiscountPrice = parseFloat($('#discount_price').val()) || 0;
            const mainPrice = productDiscountPrice > 0 ? productDiscountPrice : productPrice;
            const extraPrice = parseFloat($row.find('.extraPriceForm').val()) || 0;
            parseFloat($row.find('.attrDiscount').text(value));
            const totalExtraPrice = mainPrice + extraPrice;
            let discountValue = value;
            if (value > totalExtraPrice) {
                discountValue = totalExtraPrice;
                $(this).val(totalExtraPrice.toFixed(2));
                parseFloat($row.find('.attrDiscount').text(totalExtraPrice.toFixed(2)));
            }
            const totalPrice = totalExtraPrice - discountValue;
            $row.find('.totalVariationPrice').text(totalPrice.toFixed(2));
        });


        $('.variationSelect').on('change', function() {
            // Get the selected options
            var selectedOptions = $(this).find(':selected');

            selectedOptions.each(function() {
                var variationName = $(this).data('name');
                var variationId = $(this).val();

                // Check if the row already exists
                if (!$(`#variation_${variationId}_Box`).length) {
                    appendNewVariation(variationName, variationId)
                }
            });

            $(this).find(':not(:selected)').each(function() {
                var variationId = $(this).val();
                $(`#variation_${variationId}_Box`).remove();
            });

        });

        // added new variation
        function appendNewVariation(name, id) {
            $('#variationSection').append(`
                <div class="border rounded p-0 position-relative overflow-hidden" id="variation_${id}_Box" style="border-color: #6c757d !important">
                    <p class="fw-medium box-title">
                        Variation for <span class="fw-bold">${name}</span>
                        <input type="hidden" name="variations[${id}][name]" value="${name}">
                    </p>
                    <div class="p-2 border border-secondary">
                        <label>Select Attributes</label>
                        <select name="variations[${id}][attributes]" id="variation_${id}_attributeSelect" class="form-control variationSelect2" multiple data-placeholder="Select Attributes" onchange="changeAttribute(${id})"></select>
                    </div>

                    <div class="p-3 d-flex flex-column gap-3" id="variation_${id}_attributeBox">
                        <p class="fst-italic text-muted" id="noAttr">No Attribute Selected</p>
                    </div>
                </div>`);
            $('.variationSelect2').select2();
            fetchAttributes(id)
        }

        function fetchAttributes(variationID) {
            $.ajax({
                url: '/api/attributes?variation_id=' + variationID,
                type: "GET",
                dataType: "json",
                success: function(data) {
                    var attributeSection = $(`#variation_${variationID}_attributeSelect`);
                    attributeSection.empty();

                    $.each(data.data.attributes, function(key, value) {
                        attributeSection.append(`
                                <option value="${value.id}" data-name="${value.name}">
                                    ${value.name}
                                </option>
                            `);
                    });
                    attributeSection.trigger('change');
                },
                error: function(xhr, status, error) {
                    console.log(error);
                }
            });
        }

        function changeAttribute(varID) {
            var selectedOptions = $(`#variation_${varID}_attributeSelect`).find(':selected');

            selectedOptions.each(function() {
                var name = $(this).data('name');
                var Id = $(this).val();

                if (!$(`#attribute${Id}`).length) {
                    appendAttribute(varID, name, Id)
                }
                setupSku()
            });

            $(`#variation_${varID}_attributeSelect`).find(':not(:selected)').each(function() {
                var attrId = $(this).val();
                $(`#attribute${attrId}`).remove();
            });

            const productPrice = parseFloat($('#price').val()) || 0;
            const productDiscountPrice = parseFloat($('#discount_price').val()) || 0;
            const mainPrice = productDiscountPrice > 0 ? productDiscountPrice : productPrice;

            setDefaultPrice(varID, null, mainPrice);
        }

        function appendAttribute(varID, attrName, attrID) {
            var productPrice = $('#price').val() ?? 0;
            var productDiscountPrice = $('#discount_price').val() ?? 0;
            var mainPrice = productDiscountPrice > 0 ? productDiscountPrice : productPrice;

            $('#noAttr').remove();

            $(`#variation_${varID}_attributeBox`).append(`
            <div class="card border-info-subtle" id="attribute${attrID}">
                <div class="card-header d-flex align-items-center justify-content-between">
                    <h5 class="card-title m-0">
                        <span class="fz-20">${attrName}</span> <small class="text-muted">(Attribute)</small>
                        <input type="hidden" name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][name]" value="${attrName}">
                    </h5>
                    <div>
                        <span>Default Price</span>
                        <label class="switch mb-0" data-bs-toggle="tooltip" data-bs-placement="left"
                            data-bs-title="This is default price">
                            <input type="checkbox" name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][default]" onclick="setDefaultPrice(${varID}, ${attrID}, ${mainPrice})">
                            <span class="slider round"></span>
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="card-body">
                    <div class="row gy-3">
                        <div class="col-lg-7">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-md-5">
                                    <label>Extra Price</label>
                                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-2 border p-2 rounded">
                                        <span class="fw-bolder mainProductPrice" data-price="${mainPrice}">${mainPrice}</span>
                                        <span class="bg-light px-2 py-1 rounded">
                                            <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
                                        </span>
                                        <input type="text" class="form-control extraPriceForm"
                                            name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][price]"
                                            placeholder="Extra Price from default price"
                                            oninput="this.value = this.value.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, '').replace(/^(d*.d{0,2}|d*)$/, '$1');" />
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-5">
                                    <label>Discount Price</label>
                                    <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-2 border p-2 rounded">
                                        <span class="bg-light px-2 py-1 rounded">
                                            <i class="fa-solid fa-minus"></i>
                                        </span>
                                        <input type="text" class="form-control extraDiscountPriceForm"
                                            name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][discount]"
                                            placeholder="Discount Price from default price"
                                            oninput="this.value = this.value.replace(/[^0-9.]/g, '').replace(/^(d*.d{0,2}|d*)$/, '$1');" />
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-2">
                                </div>
                                <div class="mt-3 ms-2">
                                    <span class="totalVarPrice">${mainPrice}</span>-<span class="attrDiscount">0</span>=<span class="totalVariationPrice">${mainPrice}</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-lg-5">
                            <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-3" id="variation_${varID}_attribute_${attrID}_thumbnails">
                                <div id="attribute${attrID}Thumbnail0" class="dropzone-container">
                                    <label for="attribute_${attrID}_thumbnail0" class="additionThumbnail">
                                        <img src="https://admin.pcbstore.net/default/upload.png" id="attribute${attrID}preview0" class="dropzone-area" alt="" width="100%" height="100%" />
                                        <button onclick="removeThumbnail('attribute${attrID}Thumbnail0')" id="removeAttribute${attrID}Thumbnail0" type="button" class="delete btn btn-sm btn-outline-danger circleIcon" style="display: none">
                                            <img src="https://admin.pcbstore.net/assets/icons-admin/trash.svg" loading="lazy" alt="trash" />
                                        </button>
                                    </label>
                                    <input id="attribute_${attrID}_thumbnail0" accept="image/*" type="file" data-crop="true" name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][thumbnails][0][file]" class="d-none" onchange="previewAdditionalFile(event, 'attribute${attrID}preview0', 'removeAttribute${attrID}Thumbnail0', ${attrID}, ${varID}, 0)" data-preview="attribute${attrID}preview0" />

                                    <input type="hidden" name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][thumbnails][0][id]" />
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>`);
        }

        // form submit loader
        $('form').on('submit', function() {
            var submitButton = $(this).find('button[type="submit"]');

            submitButton.prop('disabled', true);
            submitButton.removeClass('px-5');

            submitButton.html(`
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-1">
                <div class="spinner-border" role="status"></div>
                <span>Submitting...</span>
            </div>`)
        });

        // set default price
        function setDefaultPrice(varID, clickedAttrID = null, mainPrice = 0) {
            var selectedOptions = $(`#variation_${varID}_attributeSelect`).find(':selected');
            var hasSelected = false;
            totalVariationPrice = mainPrice;
            console.log('mainasdfk',mainPrice);

            selectedOptions.each(function() {
                var attrId = $(this).val();
                let checkbox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrId}][default]"]`);
                let priceBox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrId}][price]"]`);
                let discountBox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrId}][discount]"]`);
                // let totalVariation = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrId}][totalVariation]"]`);
                let card = $(`#attribute${attrId}`);

                card.find('.totalVariationPrice').text(mainPrice.toFixed(2));
                card.find('.totalVarPrice').text(mainPrice.toFixed(2));
                card.find('.attrDiscount').text(0);

                checkbox.prop('checked', false);
                priceBox.attr('readonly', false).val('');
                discountBox.attr('readonly', false).val('');
                // totalVariation.val(mainPrice);
            });

            if (clickedAttrID) {
                let clickedCheckbox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${clickedAttrID}][default]"]`);
                let clickedPriceBox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${clickedAttrID}][price]"]`);
                let clickedDiscountBox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${clickedAttrID}][discount]"]`);

                if (clickedCheckbox.is(':checked')) {
                    clickedCheckbox.prop('checked', false);
                    clickedPriceBox.attr('readonly', false).val('');
                    clickedDiscountBox.attr('readonly', false).val('');
                } else {
                    clickedCheckbox.prop('checked', true);
                    clickedPriceBox.attr('readonly', true).val(0);
                    clickedDiscountBox.attr('readonly', true).val(0);
                }
            } else {
                selectedOptions.each(function() {
                    if (!hasSelected) {
                        var attrId = $(this).val();
                        let checkbox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrId}][default]"]`);
                        let priceBox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrId}][price]"]`);
                        let discountBox = $(`input[name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrId}][discount]"]`);

                        checkbox.prop('checked', true);
                        priceBox.attr('readonly', true).val(0);
                        discountBox.attr('readonly', true).val(0);
                        hasSelected = true;
                    }
                });
            }
        }
    </script>

    <!-- additional thumbnail script -->
    <script>
        var thumbnailCount = 200;

        const previewAdditionalFile = (event, id, removeId, attrID, varID, thumbnailID) => {
            var reader = new FileReader();
            reader.onload = function() {
                var output = document.getElementById(id);
                output.src = reader.result;
            };
            reader.readAsDataURL(event.target.files[0]);

            document.getElementById(removeId).style.display = 'block';

            html = `
            <div id="attribute${attrID}Thumbnail${thumbnailCount}" class="dropzone-container">
                <label for="attribute_${attrID}_thumbnail${thumbnailCount}" class="additionThumbnail">
                    <img src="https://admin.pcbstore.net/default/upload.png" id="attribute${attrID}preview${thumbnailCount}" alt="" width="100%" height="100%" class="dropzone-area" />
                    <button onclick="removeThumbnail('attribute${attrID}Thumbnail${thumbnailCount}')" id="removeAttribute${attrID}Thumbnail${thumbnailCount}" type="button" class="delete btn btn-sm btn-outline-danger circleIcon" style="display: none">
                        <img src="https://admin.pcbstore.net/assets/icons-admin/trash.svg" loading="lazy" alt="trash" />
                    </button>
                </label>
                <input id="attribute_${attrID}_thumbnail${thumbnailCount}" accept="image/*" type="file" data-crop="true" name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][thumbnails][${thumbnailCount}][file]" class="d-none" onchange="previewAdditionalFile(event, 'attribute${attrID}preview${thumbnailCount}', 'removeAttribute${attrID}Thumbnail${thumbnailCount}', ${attrID}, ${varID}, ${thumbnailCount})" data-preview="attribute${attrID}preview${thumbnailCount}" />

                <input type="hidden" name="variations[${varID}][attributes][${attrID}][thumbnails][${thumbnailCount}][id]" />
            </div>`;

            $(`#variation_${varID}_attribute_${attrID}_thumbnails`).append(html);

            // Set the new onchange attribute
            var inputElement = event.target;
            let previewId = `attribute${attrID}preview${thumbnailID}`
            var newOnchangeFunction = `onlyPreviewFile(event, '${previewId}')`;
            inputElement.setAttribute("onchange", newOnchangeFunction);

            // increment count
            thumbnailCount++;
        }

        const onlyPreviewFile = (event, id) => {
            var reader = new FileReader();
            reader.onload = function() {
                var output = document.getElementById(id);
                output.src = reader.result;
            };
            reader.readAsDataURL(event.target.files[0]);
        }

        const removeThumbnail = (thumbnailId) => {
            const thumbnailToRemove = document.getElementById(thumbnailId);
            if (thumbnailToRemove) {
                thumbnailToRemove.parentNode.removeChild(thumbnailToRemove);
            }
        }

        const generateCode = () => {
            const code = document.getElementById('barcode');
            code.value = Math.floor(Math.random() * 900000) + 100000;
        }
    </script>

    <!-- color select2 script -->
    <script>
        function formatState(state) {
            if (!state.id) {
                return state.text;
            }
            var $state = $(
                '<span class="d-flex align-items-center"> <span style="background-color:' + state.element.dataset
                .color +
                ';width:20px;height:20px;display:inline-block; border-radius:5px;margin-right:5px;"></span>' + state
                .text + '</span>'
            );
            return $state;
        };

        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('.colorSelect').select2({
                templateResult: formatState
            });
        });
    </script>

    <script>
        correctULTagFromQuill = (str) => {
            if (str) {
                let re = /(<ol><li data-list="bullet">)(.*?)(<\/ol>)/;
                let strArr = str.split(re);

                while (
                    strArr.findIndex((ele) => ele === '<ol><li data-list="bullet">') !== -1
                ) {
                    let index = strArr.findIndex(
                        (ele) => ele === '<ol><li data-list="bullet">'
                    );
                    if (index) {
                        strArr[index] = '<ul><li data-list="bullet">';
                        let endTagIndex = strArr.findIndex((ele) => ele === "</ol>");
                        strArr[endTagIndex] = "</ul>";
                    }
                }
                return strArr.join("");
            }
            return str;
        };

        const quill2 = new Quill('#specificationEditor', {

                        'font': []
                    }],
                    ['bold', 'italic', 'underline', 'strike', 'blockquote'],
                    [{
                        'list': 'ordered'
                    }, {
                        'list': 'bullet'
                    }],
                    [{
                        'align': []
                    }],
                    [{
                        'script': 'sub'
                    }, {
                        'script': 'super'
                    }],
                    [{
                        'indent': '-1'
                    }, {
                        'indent': '+1'
                    }],
                    [{
                        'direction': 'rtl'
                    }],
                    [{
                        'color': []
                    }, {
                        'background': []
                    }],
                    ['link', 'image', 'video', 'formula'],
                    ['table']
                ],
                table: true,
            }
        });

        quill2.on('text-change', function(delta, oldDelta, source) {
            document.getElementById('specification').value = correctULTagFromQuill(quill2.root.innerHTML);
        });

    <script>
        $(document).ready(function() {
            $('input.category-checkbox').on('change', function() {
                handleCategoryCheckbox($(this));
            });

            $('input.category-checkbox:checked').each(function() {
                handleCategoryCheckbox($(this));
            });

            const $categoryContainer = $('#categoryTree');
            const $checked = $categoryContainer.find('input.category-checkbox:checked');
            let $targetLi = null;
            $checked.each(function() {
                const depth = $(this).parents('ul.category-tree').length;
                console.log(depth);
                if (depth === 2) {
                    $targetLi = $(this).closest('li');
                    console.log($targetLi);
                    return false;
                }
                if (depth > 2) {
                    $targetLi = $(this).closest('ul.category-tree').parent('li');
                    console.log($targetLi);
                    return false;
                }
            });

            if (!$targetLi && $checked.length) {
                $targetLi = $checked.first().closest('li');
            }
            if ($targetLi) {
                const top = $targetLi.position().top || 0;
                $categoryContainer.animate({
                    scrollTop: $categoryContainer.scrollTop() + top - 150
                }, 300);
            }


            function handleCategoryCheckbox($checkbox) {
                var categoryId = $checkbox.val();
                var $attributeCategory = $('.attributeCategory-' + categoryId);
                var $tree = $('.categoryAttribute-tree-' + categoryId);

                if ($checkbox.is(':checked')) {
                    $attributeCategory.removeClass('d-none');
                    $tree.removeClass('d-none');
                    $tree.find('.attributeBox').removeAttr('disabled');
                    $tree.closest('li').find('.attributeCategoryBox').prop('checked', true);
                } else {
                    $attributeCategory.addClass('d-none');
                    $tree.addClass('d-none');
                    $tree.find('.attributeBox').prop('checked', false).attr('disabled', true);
                    $tree.closest('li').find('.attributeCategoryBox').prop('checked', false).attr('disabled', true);
                }
            }
        });
    </script>



    

    <script>
        let cropper;
        let activeInput = null;
        let activePreview = null;

        let activeOriginalName = null;

        document.addEventListener('change', function(e) {
            const input = e.target.closest(
                '[data-crop="true"]');

            if (!input || !input.matches('input[type="file"]')) return;

            const file = input.files[0];
            if (!file) return;

            activeInput = input;
            activePreview = document.getElementById(input.dataset.preview);
            activeOriginalName = file.name;

            const reader = new FileReader();
            reader.onload = function(event) {
                const image = document.getElementById('imageToCrop');
                image.src = event.target.result;

                const modal = new bootstrap.Modal(document.getElementById('cropperModal'));
                modal.show();

                if (cropper) cropper.destroy();
                cropper = new Cropper(image, {
                    aspectRatio: 1,
                    viewMode: 1,
                    autoCropArea: 1,
                });
            };
            reader.readAsDataURL(file);
        });

        document.getElementById('cropAndSave').addEventListener('click', function() {
            if (!cropper || !activeInput || !activePreview) return;

            cropper.getCroppedCanvas({
                width: 500,
                height: 500
            }).toBlob(function(blob) {
                const baseName = (activeOriginalName ?? 'image').replace(/\.[^/.]+$/, '') || 'image';
                const croppedFileName = `${baseName}.webp`;
                const croppedFile = new File([blob], croppedFileName, {
                    type: 'image/webp'
                });

                const dataTransfer = new DataTransfer();
                dataTransfer.items.add(croppedFile);
                activeInput.files = dataTransfer.files;

                const reader = new FileReader();
                reader.onload = function(e) {

                    if (activePreview) {
                        activePreview.src = e.target.result;
                    } else {
                        console.error("activePreview is unexpectedly null inside reader.onload!");
                    }
                    bootstrap.Modal.getInstance(document.getElementById('cropperModal')).hide();
                    cropper.destroy();
                    cropper = null;
                    activeInput = null;
                    activePreview = null;
                };
                reader.readAsDataURL(croppedFile);
            });
        });
    </script>



    <script>
        document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
            const dropzone = e.target.closest('.dropzone-area');
            if (!dropzone) return;

            const container = dropzone.closest('.dropzone-container');
            if (!container) return;

            const fileInput = container.querySelector('input[type="file"][data-crop="true"]');
            if (fileInput && !fileInput.disabled) {
                e.preventDefault();
                fileInput.click();
            }
        }, {
            passive: false
        });

        document.addEventListener('dragover', function(e) {
            const dropzone = e.target.closest('.dropzone-area');
            if (!dropzone) return;
            e.preventDefault();
            dropzone.classList.add('dragover');
        });

        document.addEventListener('dragleave', function(e) {
            const dropzone = e.target.closest('.dropzone-area');
            if (!dropzone) return;
            dropzone.classList.remove('dragover');
        });

        document.addEventListener('drop', function(e) {
            const dropzone = e.target.closest('.dropzone-area');
            if (!dropzone) return;
            e.preventDefault();
            dropzone.classList.remove('dragover');

            const container = dropzone.closest('.dropzone-container');
            if (!container) return;

            const fileInput = container.querySelector('input[type="file"][data-crop="true"]');
            if (!fileInput) return;

            const file = e.dataTransfer.files[0];
            if (file && file.type.startsWith('image/')) {

                const dataTransfer = new DataTransfer();
                dataTransfer.items.add(file);
                fileInput.files = dataTransfer.files;

                fileInput.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', {
                    bubbles: true
                }));
            }
        });
    </script>
    <script>
        function addFaq() {
            let faqRow = `
                <div class="row faqRow mb-2">
                    <input type="hidden" name="faq_id[]" value="">
                    <div class="col-5">
                        <div>
        <input type="text" name="question[]" id="question[]" class="form-control " value="" placeholder="Faq Question"     maxlength="255"  >
    </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-5">
                        <div>
        <input type="text" name="answer[]" id="answer[]" class="form-control " value="" placeholder="Faq Answer"     maxlength="255"  >
    </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-2">
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-danger" onclick="deleteFaq(this)">
                            <i class="fa-solid fa-minus"></i>
                        </button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            `;
            document.getElementById('faqContainer').insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', faqRow);
        }

        function deleteFaq(button) {
            button.closest('.faqRow').remove();
        }

        let nextGroupIndex = 5;

        function addSpec(button) {
            const groupEl = button.closest('.specGroup');
            const groupIndex = groupEl.dataset.index;
            // read and increment per-group item counter
            let itemCounter = parseInt(groupEl.dataset.itemCounter, 10);
            const itemIndex = itemCounter; // use current counter as index
            groupEl.dataset.itemCounter = itemCounter + 1;

            const rowHTML = `
            <div class="row specRow mb-2" data-item-index="${itemIndex}">
            <div class="col-5">
                <input name="specs[${groupIndex}][items][${itemIndex}][name]" type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Name" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-5">
                <input name="specs[${groupIndex}][items][${itemIndex}][title]" type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Title" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-2 d-flex align-items-center">
                <span class="btn btn-sm btn-light me-1 item-drag-handle" style="cursor: move;"><i class="fa-solid fa-grip-vertical"></i></span>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-danger" onclick="deleteSpec(this)">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-minus"></i>
                </button>
            </div>
            </div>
        `;

            groupEl.querySelector('.specContainer').insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', rowHTML);
        }

        function deleteSpec(button) {
            const row = button.closest('.specRow');
            if (row) row.remove();
        }

        function addSpecGroup() {
            const container = document.querySelector('.specGroupContainer');
            const gIndex = nextGroupIndex++;
            const groupHTML = `
            <div class="specGroup mt-3" data-index="${gIndex}" data-item-counter="1">
            <div class="row mb-2">
                <div class="col-4 d-flex align-items-start">
                <span class="btn btn-sm btn-light me-2 group-drag-handle" style="cursor: move;"><i class="fa-solid fa-grip-vertical"></i></span>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-danger me-2" onclick="removeSpecGroup(this)">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-minus"></i>
                </button>
                <input name="specs[${gIndex}][group_name]" type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Group Name" />
                </div>

                <div class="col-8 specContainer">
                <div class="row specRow mb-2" data-item-index="0">
                    <div class="col-5">
                    <input name="specs[${gIndex}][items][0][name]" type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Name" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-5">
                    <input name="specs[${gIndex}][items][0][title]" type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Title" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-2 d-flex align-items-center">
                    <span class="btn btn-sm btn-light me-1 item-drag-handle" style="cursor: move;"><i class="fa-solid fa-grip-vertical"></i></span>
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" onclick="addSpec(this)">
                        <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
                    </button>
                    </div>
                </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            </div>
        `;
            container.insertAdjacentHTML('beforeend', groupHTML);

            // Initialize Sortable for the new group's specContainer
            const newGroup = container.lastElementChild;
            const newSpecContainer = newGroup.querySelector('.specContainer');
            initItemSortable(newSpecContainer);
        }

        function removeSpecGroup(button) {
            const group = button.closest('.specGroup');
            if (group) group.remove();
        }
    </script>
    <script>
        let extraCount = 1;

        const previewExtraFile = (event, previewId, removeId) => {
            const file = event.target.files[0];
            if (!file) return;

            const reader = new FileReader();
            reader.onload = function() {
                const preview = document.getElementById(previewId);
                if (preview) preview.src = reader.result;
            };
            reader.readAsDataURL(file);

            const removeBtn = document.getElementById(removeId);
            if (removeBtn) removeBtn.style.display = 'block';

            if (event.target.id === `extraFile${extraCount}`) {
                addNewExtraBox();
            }
        };

        const addNewExtraBox = () => {
            extraCount++;

            const newBoxId = `extraBox${extraCount}`;
            const newInputId = `extraFile${extraCount}`;
            const newPreviewId = `extraPreview${extraCount}`;
            const newRemoveId = `removeExtra${extraCount}`;

            const newBox = document.createElement('div');
            newBox.classList.add('col-6', 'mb-2', 'dropzone-container');
            newBox.id = newBoxId;

            newBox.innerHTML = `
                <label for="${newInputId}" class="extraThumbnail">
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/500x500/f1f5f9/png" id="${newPreviewId}" alt="" width="100%" class="dropzone-area">
                    <button onclick="removeExtraBox('${newBoxId}')" id="${newRemoveId}"
                        type="button" class="delete btn btn-sm btn-outline-danger circleIcon"
                        style="display: none">
                        <img src="https://admin.pcbstore.net/assets/icons-admin/trash.svg" loading="lazy" alt="trash" />
                    </button>
                </label>
                <input id="${newInputId}" accept="image/*" type="file" data-crop="true"
                    name="extraThumbnail[]" class="d-none" data-preview="${newPreviewId}"
                    onchange="previewExtraFile(event, '${newPreviewId}', '${newRemoveId}')">
            `;

            document.getElementById('extraElements').appendChild(newBox);
        };


        const removeExtraBox = (boxId) => {
            const box = document.getElementById(boxId);
            if (box) box.remove();
        };
    </script>
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/sortablejs@latest/Sortable.min.js"></script>
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
            // Group Sorting
            const groupContainer = document.querySelector('.specGroupContainer');
            if (groupContainer) {
                new Sortable(groupContainer, {
                    animation: 150,
                    handle: '.group-drag-handle',
                    onEnd: function() {
                        reIndexSpecs();
                    }
                });
            }

            // Item Sorting (Initialize for existing groups)
            document.querySelectorAll('.specContainer').forEach(function(el) {
                initItemSortable(el);
            });
        });

        function initItemSortable(el) {
            new Sortable(el, {
                animation: 150,
                handle: '.item-drag-handle',
                onEnd: function() {
                    reIndexSpecs();
                }
            });
        }

        function reIndexSpecs() {
            const groups = document.querySelectorAll('.specGroup');
            groups.forEach((group, groupIndex) => {
                // Update group name
                const groupNameInput = group.querySelector('input[name*="[group_name]"]');
                if (groupNameInput) {
                    groupNameInput.setAttribute('name', `specs[${groupIndex}][group_name]`);
                }

                // Update items
                const items = group.querySelectorAll('.specRow');
                items.forEach((item, itemIndex) => {
                    const nameInput = item.querySelector('input[placeholder="Name"]');
                    const titleInput = item.querySelector('input[placeholder="Title"]');

                    if (nameInput) nameInput.setAttribute('name',
                        `specs[${groupIndex}][items][${itemIndex}][name]`);
                    if (titleInput) titleInput.setAttribute('name',
                        `specs[${groupIndex}][items][${itemIndex}][title]`);
                });
            });
        }
    </script>

    
    
    
    
    
    
    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
            var root = document.documentElement;

            // Get the value of --theme-color
            var themeColor = getComputedStyle(root).getPropertyValue("--theme-color");

            $(".deleteConfirm").on("click", function(e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                const url = $(this).attr("href");
                Swal.fire({
                    title: "Are you sure?",
                    text: 'You will not be able to revert this!',
                    icon: "warning",
                    showCancelButton: true,
                    confirmButtonColor: themeColor,
                    cancelButtonColor: "#d33",
                    confirmButtonText: "Yes, delete it!",
                }).then((result) => {
                    if (result.isConfirmed) {
                        window.location.href = url;
                    }
                });
            });

            $(".logout").on("click", function(e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                Swal.fire({
                    title: "Are you sure?",
                    text: "Are you sure you want to log out?",
                    icon: "warning",
                    showCancelButton: true,
                    confirmButtonColor: themeColor,
                    cancelButtonColor: "#d33",
                    confirmButtonText: "Yes, Logout!",
                }).then((result) => {
                    if (result.isConfirmed) {
                        document.getElementById("logoutForm").submit();
                    }
                });
            });

            // form submit loader
            $('form').on('submit', function() {
                var submitButton = $(this).find('button[type="submit"]');

                submitButton.prop('disabled', true);
                submitButton.removeClass('px-5');

                submitButton.html(`<div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-1">
                    <div class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm" role="status"></div>
                    <span>Loading...</span>
                </div>`)
            });
        });
    </script>

    <script>
        // show active menu
        $(document).ready(function() {
            let activeMenuItem = $('.vertical-nav-menu .menu.active');

            if (activeMenuItem.length) {
                activeMenuItem.closest('.collapse').addClass('show');

                let sidebar = $('.scrollbar-sidebar');

                let offsetTop = activeMenuItem.offset().top;
                let sidebarTop = sidebar.offset().top;
                let scrollPosition = sidebar.scrollTop() + (offsetTop - sidebarTop) - 80;

                sidebar.animate({
                    scrollTop: scrollPosition
                }, 500);
            }
        });
    </script>

    <script>
        $(function() {
            $('input[name="date_range"]').daterangepicker({
                autoUpdateInput: false,
                locale: {
                    format: 'YYYY-MM-DD',
                    cancelLabel: 'Clear'
                },
                ranges: {
                    'Today': [moment(), moment()],
                    'Yesterday': [moment().subtract(1, 'days'), moment().subtract(1, 'days')],
                    'Last 7 Days': [moment().subtract(6, 'days'), moment()],
                    'Last 30 Days': [moment().subtract(29, 'days'), moment()],
                    'This Month': [moment().startOf('month'), moment().endOf('month')],
                    'Last Month': [moment().subtract(1, 'month').startOf('month'), moment().subtract(1,
                        'month').endOf('month')]
                }
            });
            $('input[name="date_range"]').on('apply.daterangepicker', function(ev, picker) {
                $(this).val(
                    picker.startDate.format('YYYY-MM-DD') + ' - ' + picker.endDate.format('YYYY-MM-DD')
                );
            });
            $('input[name="date_range"]').on('cancel.daterangepicker', function(ev, picker) {
                $(this).val('');
            });
        });
    </script>
